---
import { SAINTS } from "../lib/data";
import {
  AMERICA_MOVEMENT_I,
  AMERICA_MOVEMENT_II,
  AMERICA_AWAITING,
  type AmericaSaint,
} from "../lib/america";
import { withBase } from "../lib/format";
import { saintAvatar } from "../lib/icons";
import DomeMark from "./icons/DomeMark.astro";
import EyebrowRule from "./EyebrowRule.astro";
import AmericaMovement from "./AmericaMovement.astro";

const saintMap = new Map(SAINTS.map((s) => [s.id, s]));

const prep = (s: AmericaSaint) => ({
  s,
  hit: saintMap.get(s.id),
  catSlug: "t-" + s.cat.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]+/g, "-"),
});
const movement1 = AMERICA_MOVEMENT_I.map(prep);
const movement2 = AMERICA_MOVEMENT_II.map(prep);

const awaiting = AMERICA_AWAITING.map((s) => ({
  s,
  reposed: s.reposedYear || (s.years.split("–").pop() || "").trim(),
}));
---

{/* ---------- hero (ivory) ---------- */}
<section class="am-hero">
  <div class="dome-bg"><DomeMark w={460} color="var(--byz)" /></div>
  <div class="inner">
    <EyebrowRule label="The Saints of America" />
    <h1>A Pilgrimage of Hope</h1>
    <p class="am-hero-tagline">The Holy People of America</p>
    <blockquote class="am-verse">
      &ldquo;The kingdom of heaven is like a grain of mustard seed that a man
      took and sowed in his field. It is the smallest of all seeds, but when it
      has grown it is larger than all the garden plants and becomes a tree, so
      that the birds of the air come and make nests in its branches.&rdquo;
      <cite>Matthew 13 : 31&ndash;32</cite>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

{/* ---------- opening essay (paper) ---------- */}
<section class="am-essay">
  <div class="am-essay-inner">
    <p class="dropcap">
      When first approaching Orthodoxy, it can seem as if it is far away. You
      might wonder: Where has the Church been this whole time? Why does America
      feel as though it has been left to wander in the desert?
    </p>
    <p>
      The thing is, the Church has been here all along. Some might say she has
      existed since before the foundations of the world. America, on the other
      hand, is young. Though the Church has grown slowly here, she is here.
    </p>
    <figure class="am-scripture">
      <blockquote>
        &ldquo;The kingdom of heaven is like leaven that a woman took and hid in
        three measures of flour, till it was all leavened.&rdquo;
      </blockquote>
      <figcaption>Matthew 13:33</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <p>
      Slowly, and often hidden from the world, Christ has been planting seeds of
      holiness in this land.
    </p>
    <p>
      The holy people of America remind us that Orthodoxy is not only something
      ancient and far away. It is alive here. Saints crossed oceans, endured
      loneliness, built churches, prayed in wilderness places, served the poor,
      and healed the wounded.
    </p>
    <p>
      On this page you will find a small gathering of witnesses &mdash;
      canonized saints, righteous elders, missionaries, monastics, martyrs,
      mothers, priests, and faithful servants whose lives show that God is still
      working in this land.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

{
  /* ---------- the gallery (deep navy ground, three gilded panels) ---------- */
}
<div class="am-gallery">
  <AmericaMovement
    title="They Came from Across the Sea"
    lede="Saints that came to us from other places."
    tone="garnet"
  >
    {
      movement1.map(({ s, hit, catSlug }) => {
        const Tag = hit ? "a" : "div";
        return (
          <Tag
            class={`pga-card${hit ? " clickable" : ""}`}
            data-saint={hit?.id}
            href={hit ? withBase(`saint/${hit.id}`) : undefined}
          >
            <div
              class="portrait"
              set:html={saintAvatar({ name: s.name }, 84, 104, {
                type: s.cat,
              })}
            />
            <div class="body">
              <h3>{s.name}</h3>
              {s.epithet && <div class="epithet">{s.epithet}</div>}
              <div class="years">{s.years}</div>
              <span class={`tag ${catSlug}`}>
                <i />
                {s.cat}
              </span>
              <p>{s.contribution}</p>
              <div class="foot">
                <span class="feast">Feast · {s.feast}</span>
                <span class="glor">Glorified {s.glorified}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Tag>
        );
      })
    }
  </AmericaMovement>

  <AmericaMovement
    title="Those Born of This Land"
    lede="Saints from America"
    tone="forest"
  >
    {
      movement2.map(({ s, hit, catSlug }) => {
        const Tag = hit ? "a" : "div";
        return (
          <Tag
            class={`pga-card${hit ? " clickable" : ""}`}
            data-saint={hit?.id}
            href={hit ? withBase(`saint/${hit.id}`) : undefined}
          >
            <div
              class="portrait"
              set:html={saintAvatar({ name: s.name }, 84, 104, {
                type: s.cat,
              })}
            />
            <div class="body">
              <h3>{s.name}</h3>
              {s.epithet && <div class="epithet">{s.epithet}</div>}
              <div class="years">{s.years}</div>
              <span class={`tag ${catSlug}`}>
                <i />
                {s.cat}
              </span>
              <p>{s.contribution}</p>
              <div class="foot">
                <span class="feast">Feast · {s.feast}</span>
                <span class="glor">Glorified {s.glorified}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </Tag>
        );
      })
    }
  </AmericaMovement>

  <AmericaMovement
    title="The Witnesses of Our Time"
    lede="The work is not finished. These reposed servants are held in living memory by the faithful — remembered with love, though not yet formally glorified by the Church."
    tone="plum"
    tail
  >
    {
      awaiting.map(({ s, reposed }) => (
        <div class="pga-card">
          <div
            class="portrait"
            set:html={saintAvatar({ name: s.name }, 84, 104, {
              awaiting: true,
            })}
          />
          <div class="body">
            <h3>{s.name}</h3>
            {s.epithet && <div class="epithet">{s.epithet}</div>}
            <div class="years">
              {s.years || (reposed ? `† Reposed ${reposed}` : "")}
            </div>
            <div class="badges">
              <span class="tag t-venerated">
                <i />
                {s.role}
              </span>
              <span class="tag t-venerated solid">Not yet glorified</span>
            </div>
            <p>{s.contribution}</p>
            <div class="foot">
              <span class="place">{s.place}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))
    }
  </AmericaMovement>
</div>

{/* ---------- the story continues (paper) ---------- */}
<section class="am-continues">
  <div class="am-essay-inner">
    <div class="am-continues-head">
      <h2>The Story Continues</h2>
      <div class="rule"><span class="dot"></span></div>
    </div>
    <p>
      The holy people on this page are only a small glimpse of what God has
      done&mdash;and continues to do&mdash;in America.
    </p>
    <p>
      Throughout North America, monasteries continue to flourish, relics
      continue to be venerated, pilgrims continue to receive comfort, and lives
      continue to be transformed through Christ and His Church.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Kingdom often grows quietly, like leaven hidden in dough or a mustard
      seed planted in the earth. Yet the very existence of Orthodox churches,
      monasteries, saints, and faithful Christians throughout this land is
      evidence that God has not forgotten America.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
